-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing events to one per subscription + event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_subscriptions_enriched.sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with user and company information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        u.company_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    company_id
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_billing_with_dimensions.sql
-- Join billing events with subscriptions and dimensions
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.subscription_id,
        b.event_month,
        b.amount,
        se.user_id,
        se.plan_id,
        se.company_id,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_enriched') }} se
        ON se.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = se.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = se.company_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    company_id,
    tier,
    industry
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/mart/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Calculate monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_month,
        tier,
        industry,
        COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM {{ ref('int_billing_with_dimensions') }}
    GROUP BY
        event_month,
        tier,
        industry
)
SELECT
    event_month AS month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM source
ORDER BY
    event_month,
    tier,
    industry
